  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This is a prospective, non-randomized study to determine the feasibility of using a new
      technique called Dynamic Substrate Mapping (DSM) to help guide the treatment of ischemic
      ventricular tachycardia (IVT). We hypothesize that DSM will lead to simpler, more effective
      ablation of IVT. Results from this study will be used to determine if further clinical
      investigation is warranted.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
